        System.out.println("Static Method Result: " + resultStatic);
        System.out.println("Instance Method Result: " + resultInstance);
    }
}
```
In this example, 'addStatic' is a static method, while 'addInstance' is an instance method. We can call the static method using the class name, while the instance method is called on an instance of the class using 'this'.

